704126f-a.text:
Emmons Avenue, south side, between Haring Street and Nostrand Avenue, showing Ewen Olson's boat Yard. This place adjoins No. 3038 on the west.

July 13, 1933
704126f-a.folder: Emmons Avenue & Haring Street, Brooklyn, NY

704128f-a.text:
3038 Emmons Avenue, south side, between Haring Street and Nostrand Avenue, showing an old frame house, occupied by one of Sheepshead Bay's boat builders. In views 2 and 3 the wing of the house can be seen touching the sidewalk; it is the result of the avenue having been widened as part of the
citys Belt Parkway system.
View 1: July 13, 1933
View 2: July 9, 1936
View 3: June 13, 1940
P. L. Sperr
